# Python Client Rules

## Architecture
- AppState is the single source of truth for all runtime state
- Controllers handle logic; Windows handle UI only
- Never put business logic in window files
- Never put UI code in controller files
- Create new files rather than bloating existing ones
- New widgets go in views/qt/ as standalone QWidget subclasses

## MT5 Adapter Rules
- Never modify execute_trade() or close_trade() signatures without updating all callers
- Always pass deviation parameter to execute_trade
- Always preserve magic=234000, ORDER_TIME_GTC, ORDER_FILLING_IOC
- Never remove the minimum lot guard (>= 0.01)

## Logging
- Use colorama: Fore.CYAN for info, Fore.YELLOW for warnings, Fore.RED for blocks/errors
- All risk-related logs prefixed [RISK]
- All copy-mode logs prefixed [COPY]
- All session logs prefixed [SESSION]
- Also call self.state.add_log() for any message that should appear in the UI log

## UI Theme (Bloomberg Terminal)
- Background: #0a0a0a, Surface: #1a1a1a, Border: #2a2a2a
- Accent: #00d4aa (teal), Error/Loss: #ff4444
- Numbers: Consolas font, Labels: Segoe UI 9pt
- No gradients, no rounded corners beyond 2px
- Apply QSS via setStyleSheet() on the main window